% \figcaption{An afternoon walk home after a wet day.}
}
\p{[[hoefner]] also presented some of the initial thoughts and work around [[yiyao]]'s PhD topic, and it was good to help clarify our thinking there. I think I will encourage all of my students not just to attend, but also to speak next year.}
\figure{
  \<html:img>[loading]{lazy}[width]{320px}[src]{\route-asset{assets/brisbane_kooka.jpeg}}%{}
%  \<html:img>[loading]{lazy}[width]{220px}[src]{\route-asset{assets/brisbane_sign.jpeg}}%{}
%  \<html:img>[loading]{lazy}[width]{220px}[src]{\route-asset{assets/brisbane_river.jpeg}}%{}
 \figcaption{The fearless kookaburra of St. Lucia campus.}
}
\p{We encountered a kookaburra at breakfast that seemed determined to steal people's sausages (swooping right in front of them). This kookaburra seems to have absolutely no fear of humans, so I was able to get very close to take a picture. Eventually we saw it smashing a piece of bread against the table to "kill" it, as they do to lizards and snakes in more natural contexts.}
